<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-12-0753 </DOCNO><TEXT>The objectives of this paper are to describe a process for developingsite restoration strategies following a nuclear weapons accident, anddemonstrate how to carry out this process using actual data from a militaryexercise. The exercise that I will be discussing is the Survey ResponseForce Exercise conducted in Savanna, Illinois in July 1986. It is calledSRFX-86 for short. While a site restoration analysis using the SRP wasconducted during the exercise, the present analysis is somewhat differentin that it contains illustrations of some of the recent revisions andenhancements to the SRP. 5 figs., 3 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>